<!--
  FIXTURE. Synthetic HL7 v3 SPL. THE DRUG AND ALL CONTENT ARE INVENTED and describe no real
  product; only the STRUCTURE is real.

  Two things the acquisition layer needs from a label, in one document:

    * IDENTITY — an <activeMoiety> coded with a UNII (codeSystem 2.16.840.1.113883.4.9), so a
      label can contribute an identity claim that must agree with PubChem/openFDA or the
      candidate is refused.
    * NESTED WARNINGS — WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS (43685-7) carries NO direct <text>; both
      warnings live in <component><section> subsections coded 42229-5. This is the shape that
      defeated the pre-e410d72 parser, and the acquisition path must still see them.
-->
